    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, why? You're saying the older guy is higher priority just because of age and \"classic distress,\" but isn't the 21-year-old showing signs of acute respiratory distress too? \n\nI'm trying to understand the reasoning behind the difference in diagnostic focus. Is there a reason you're leaning more towards a cardiac event for the first patient while framing the second patient's symptoms more around his \"agitation\"?",
